handist.collections.dist

Interface DistributedCollection<T,C extends DistributedCollection<T,C>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the object contained in the distributed collection
    C - the underlying collection itself (used for reflective operations)
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CachableChunkedList, DistBag, DistChunkedList, DistCol, DistConcurrentMap, DistConcurrentMultiMap, DistIdMap, DistMap, DistMultiMap, DistRangedMap, DistSortedMap, DistSortedMultiMap, DistSquareChunkedList

    public interface DistributedCollection<T,C extends DistributedCollection<T,C>>
    Interface representing the most basic characteristics of a distributed collection
    Author:
    Patrick Finnerty

      • writeReplace

        Object writeReplace()
             throws ObjectStreamException
        Method used to create an object which will be transferred to a remote place.

        This method is present in interface DistributedCollection to force the implementation in implementing classes. Implementation should return a LazyObjectReference instance capable of initializing the local handle of the implementing class on the remote place

        Returns:
        a LazyObjectReference of the implementing class (left to programmer's good-will)
        Throws:
        ObjectStreamException - if such an exception is thrown during the process
